Hey Guys,  New to the board, just wanted to introduce myself.  Brief description of myself.... I am only 23 but have been fishing my whole life. my dad got me into the sport while i was really young. I have two passions, hockey and fishing.  I recently just purchased a 16 ft legend with a 4 stroke 40 hp Honda, and am looking to explore some new waters this year. In the past, i have spent a lot of time fishing for pike, bass and pickerel in the summer months, while spending time in the fall hunting salmon on the credit.  With this gorgeous weather. I am heading out to the Niagara Bar Saturday, i will post a report upon my return (assuming i have some success)   Cheers,
Welcome aboard. Good luck on the bar and who is you hockey team.
Hello there and welcome. This weather is awesome, good luck at the bar.
Welcome Brucki. Heck of a set up you have there.  Best of luck this weekend.
Welcome! Careful on the bar with a 16 ft rig.
Nice?  Welcome aboard
